Border gateway protocol - Internet protocol
TCP 179 with three way handshake
Determines how the traffic flow between Autonomous systems
Its a path Vector protocol - shortest AS takes the precedence.
Collection of IP's of an organization - Autonomus number
Peers on same AS IBGP, if peers are on different AS's its EBGP.
NLRI - Network Layer routing information is the form where exchanged between routers.

BGP Message Types
BGP exchanges information via four message types:

OPEN: initiates a session, exchanging ASN and capabilities.
UPDATE: advertises or withdraws routes; carries prefix and path attributes.
KEEPALIVE: maintains session health.
NOTIFICATION: indicates errors and initiates session teardown.

OU - KN - Open, Update, Keepalive, and notification.
